Dialogue: 5,0:02:10.92,0:02:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:15.39,0:02:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:17.50,0:02:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:24.03,0:02:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:28.56,0:02:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Shigeru!
Dialogue: 5,0:02:29.70,0:02:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 5,0:02:39.92,0:02:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been taken by the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:03:02.60,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\fad(2000,0)\an9\bord0\blur0.6\p1\c&H4D4C6F&\pos(1282,66)\fscx600\fscy90}m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100
Dialogue: 2,0:02:56.57,0:03:02.60,Mushisode Title,,0,0,0,eptitle,{\fad(2000,0)\an6\blur0.6\pos(920,108)}Mud Grass
Dialogue: 5,0:03:09.56,0:03:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He's going to take a look at our warts.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:11.80,0:03:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He's just a mushi-shi, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:13.63,0:03:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't a doctor be more helpful?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:17.80,0:03:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm...
Dialogue: 5,0:03:21.68,0:03:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When did these begin to appear?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:24.24,0:03:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone started to get them three days ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:29.02,0:03:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They make the legs go numb, \Nand they're very painful.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:31.59,0:03:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's having a hard time.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:35.05,0:03:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone must have gone into the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:37.64,0:03:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder we're all infected by death.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:41.13,0:03:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"Infected by death"?
Dialogue: 5,0:03:45.90,0:03:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Four days ago, one of our fellow villagers died.
Dialogue: 5,0:03:53.42,0:03:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,According to our customs,
Dialogue: 5,0:03:56.03,0:04:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we must put our dead in one of the swamps in those mountains
Dialogue: 5,0:04:00.07,0:04:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and leave them there.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:04.06,0:04:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Within just seven days,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:05.72,0:04:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,even their bones vanish completely, leaving behind only their clothes.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:12.96,0:04:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is our belief that the dead return to the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:19.36,0:04:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,For those seven days, however,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:22.89,0:04:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,our customs also dictate \Nthat it is forbidden to enter the mountains{ until the process is complete}.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:28.64,0:04:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,According to legend,
Dialogue: 5,0:04:30.36,0:04:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,a villager long ago {once }violated that rule
Dialogue: 5,0:04:34.08,0:04:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and returned from the mountains \Nwith a pestilence that ravaged the entire village.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.96,0:04:43.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we're all afraid the same thing has happened.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:47.04,0:04:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}These must be Mukurosou seedlings.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:53.72,0:04:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's a mushi that decomposes corpses \Nand turns them into mud, down to the bones.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:59.60,0:05:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When a live animal steps on them, it inadvertently spreads them.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:04.72,0:05:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Other animals that step on the spread seedlings become their hosts.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:10.59,0:05:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The villagers' legend matches these details.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:12.89,0:05:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That confirms it.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:26.62,0:05:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Please allow me to try this.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:37.08,0:05:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It fell off!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:38.33,0:05:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The wart just fell right off!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:41.58,0:05:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the numbness in my legs is gone too!
Dialogue: 5,0:05:53.96,0:05:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ah, here they are.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:57.37,0:05:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now to just sprinkle salt on the "grass" itself...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:09.37,0:06:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:16.25,0:06:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, do you need some medicine as well?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:20.83,0:06:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you please take a look at my uncle?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:35.68,0:06:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how many times I pull them out,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:37.49,0:06:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,they grow right back.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:39.87,0:06:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When I touched them, they spread to my hands.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:47.58,0:06:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The medicine has no effect.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:50.08,0:06:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}This is a very different case from the others.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:54.67,0:06:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you the one who went into the mountains?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:01.85,0:07:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:04.54,0:07:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who passed away was my younger brother.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:08.36,0:07:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I took his son, and we went {into the mountains}up there to pay our respects.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:12.03,0:07:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Why risk violating custom?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:17.13,0:07:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All this time, I thought it was just an old wives' tale.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:23.68,0:07:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten years ago, my daughter went missing.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:30.25,0:07:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,When we checked the mountains, we only found her clothes.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:34.09,0:07:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone said it was the mountains that took her.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:39.76,0:07:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\q2}But the more I thought about it, the more I realized that \Nno one who went into the mountains back then got sick.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:45.82,0:07:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I thought it would be fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:49.88,0:07:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When you saw your brother's body, \Nwas it in the process of "returning" to the mountains?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:58.38,0:07:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:08.56,0:08:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see Dad.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:11.93,0:08:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaving him in the mountains \N all alone like that is just too mean.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:17.61,0:08:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:20.65,0:08:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go say good-bye to him one last time.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:41.66,0:08:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's this stupid grass doing on him?!{Generous timing. :)}
Dialogue: 5,0:08:44.76,0:08:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:47.12,0:08:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off!
Dialogue: 5,0:09:03.74,0:09:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad really {\i1}has{\i0} become part of the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:13.72,0:09:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This grass is continuing to live on in Dad's stead.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:31.08,0:09:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Come now, let's head back.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:40.94,0:09:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You're all alone now.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:44.04,0:09:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, would you like to come live with me?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:48.46,0:09:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You can even think of me as your father{, if you'd like}. How's that?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:52.04,0:09:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Come, let's go home.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:55.82,0:09:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't cry anymore.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:01.31,0:10:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since that night,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:03.01,0:10:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had this grass growing from my legs,
Dialogue: 5,0:10:05.92,0:10:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and it keeps on growing.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:10.33,0:10:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's strange.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:13.58,0:10:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\q2}According to records, there {\i0}have{\i1} been others who developed \Nsymptoms after {accidentally }stepping on a body that had turned to "mud."
Dialogue: 5,0:10:19.48,0:10:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}However, all of them were able to be cured by medicine.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:24.41,0:10:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So what's different in this case?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:26.43,0:10:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is it because he was related to the deceased?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:29.87,0:10:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can't be. If that were the cause, \Nthe nephew would have the same condition.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:34.04,0:10:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Something else must be afoot.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:38.33,0:10:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They intentionally went to the body's location
Dialogue: 5,0:10:40.56,0:10:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and stepped on the "mud."
Dialogue: 5,0:10:49.48,0:10:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If it got on them only when they went to pay their respects...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:54.27,0:10:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If I may ask, how did your brother die?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.38,0:11:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sousuke, please go outside for a bit.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:08.56,0:11:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He fell from a cliff.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:11.37,0:11:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He must have landed badly,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:13.40,0:11:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,because by the time I got to him, he was already...
Dialogue: 5,0:11:17.00,0:11:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He was always fond of me.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:20.60,0:11:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We were very close.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:25.90,0:11:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I took his death hard.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:34.19,0:11:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Is my uncle all better now?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:36.59,0:11:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet. There are still a few things I need to figure out.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:41.13,0:11:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, though? \NDon't you want me to treat you too?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:44.78,0:11:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:48.76,0:11:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This grass is with me in Dad's place.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:55.23,0:11:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But doesn't it hurt?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:57.15,0:12:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask me, I doubt your dad \Nwould have wanted to cause you pain.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:05.02,0:12:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I guess you need more time to think about it, \Nso I'll just leave the medicine with your uncle.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:09.66,0:12:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Use it when you're ready.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:17.66,0:12:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what sort of relationship did your dad and {your }uncle have with each other?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:25.29,0:12:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad loved my uncle.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:30.32,0:12:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little, he used to tell me lots of stories about their adventures together.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:36.43,0:12:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the last few years,
Dialogue: 5,0:12:38.97,0:12:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad didn't mention him at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:07.69,0:13:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:10.64,0:13:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, I need to talk to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.08,0:13:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Shinobu?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:16.58,0:13:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so serious.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:19.96,0:13:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you can tell me anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:40.78,0:13:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:43.88,0:13:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 5,0:13:48.68,0:13:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yuri's death...
Dialogue: 5,0:13:53.31,0:13:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all my fault.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:59.83,0:14:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know she was there...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:04.57,0:14:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and I crushed her under the cart.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:09.42,0:14:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:12.56,0:14:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I just couldn't bear to tell you...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:17.37,0:14:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I took her to the mountains.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:22.40,0:14:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 5,0:14:26.35,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:28.27,0:14:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:34.52,0:14:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I have a son of my own.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:42.48,0:14:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time I look at him, what I did haunts me.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:47.34,0:14:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how I could do such a thing—
Dialogue: 5,0:15:44.64,0:15:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fad(80,120)}Brother...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:49.92,0:15:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fad(160,120)}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:55.00,0:15:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1\fad(120,80)}I'm so sorry...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:00.51,0:16:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:03.26,0:16:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it already.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:06.06,0:16:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're dead!
Dialogue: 5,0:16:19.72,0:16:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or are you still alive after all?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:36.71,0:16:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, Sousuke...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:41.58,0:16:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A long time ago, I did something truly unforgivable to someone.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:52.64,0:16:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So if something should ever happen to me,
Dialogue: 5,0:16:56.65,0:16:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,please don't hate anyone for it.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:01.72,0:17:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't look so sad.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:04.06,0:17:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know that all of us return \Nto the mountains someday, don't you?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:11.04,0:17:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's nothing for you to worry about.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:28.84,0:17:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,After some thought, I came up with a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:33.15,0:17:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, I'd like you to hear it out.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:37.84,0:17:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Growing on your legs is a Mukurosou, or "Corpse Grass" mushi.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:42.60,0:17:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Although its most common form resembles mud,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:44.90,0:17:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it reacts to the scent of death from a dead body, \Nand it sprouts like a plant.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:50.01,0:17:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who step on its seedlings become its hosts.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:52.55,0:17:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It may try to sprout from the living, \Nbut it never grows past those "warts."
Dialogue: 5,0:17:57.39,0:17:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In your case, however,
Dialogue: 5,0:17:58.77,0:18:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it is reacting as though you are dead.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:04.03,0:18:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,One possible explanation is \Nthat the scent of death is clinging to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:12.89,0:18:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Just what are you insinuating?
Dialogue: 5,0:18:18.12,0:18:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention of pursuing \Nthis line of inquiry.{Although the CPS here is high, I really like this phrasing.}{i think the line break makes it a little easier to read in the time}
Dialogue: 5,0:18:22.24,0:18:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I am right,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:25.16,0:18:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if you somehow cleanse yourself so that no scent of death remains on your body,
Dialogue: 5,0:18:29.46,0:18:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the medicine should work.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:33.82,0:18:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If what I've said is relevant at all, you should try it.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:36.92,0:18:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That is all I have to say.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:13.77,0:19:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you kill Dad?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:18.73,0:19:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you get a crazy idea like that?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:22.43,0:19:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard everything.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:24.06,0:19:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I overheard your conversation with the mushi-shi just now.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:31.16,0:19:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you tell anyone else about what you heard?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:36.12,0:19:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:41.32,0:19:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't tell anyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:47.47,0:19:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad told me not to hate anyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:51.82,0:19:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you've been really good to me, Uncle!
Dialogue: 5,0:19:56.92,0:19:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:59.69,0:20:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What made you do such a terrible thing?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:05.95,0:20:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Back then, I simply couldn't control my rage.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:12.97,0:20:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if I had managed to control it that day,
Dialogue: 5,0:20:18.43,0:20:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure it would've ended the same way eventually.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:23.66,0:20:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you'll kill me one day too...
Dialogue: 5,0:20:36.97,0:20:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,My legs!
Dialogue: 5,0:20:38.64,0:20:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sousuke—
Dialogue: 5,0:20:41.42,0:20:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry—
Dialogue: 5,0:20:43.16,0:20:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Help—{how do you drown there wtf}
Dialogue: 5,0:21:11.36,0:21:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:11.99,0:21:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck did I just step in?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:15.68,0:21:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You should watch where you step.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:28.67,0:21:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end,
Dialogue: 5,0:21:30.82,0:21:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you couldn't make it back to the mountains...{rip sousuke}
